{"action": "input", "code": "def fill_color(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Traverse all pixels, if a non-black pixel (x, y) is surrounded by black pixels, \n    then traverse all pixels in the line: if there is another pixel (ax, ay) with \n    the same color as the pixel. Then continue to judge, if ay>y, then paint (ax, ay-1) \n    into this color. If ay<y, paint (ax,ay+1) that color. Finally assign (x,y) to black. \n    Return the modified grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    rows, cols = input_grid.shape\n    for i in range(rows):\n        for j in range(cols):\n            if input_grid[i][j] != black:\n                if i == 0 or i == rows - 1 or j == 0 or (j == cols - 1):\n                    continue\n                if input_grid[i - 1][j] == black and input_grid[i + 1][j] == black and (input_grid[i][j - 1] == black) and (input_grid[i][j + 1] == black):\n                    color = input_grid[i][j]\n                    for k in range(j + 1, cols):\n                        if input_grid[i][k] == color:\n                            input_grid[i][k - 1] = color\n                        else:\n                            break\n                    for k in range(j - 1, -1, -1):\n                        if input_grid[i][k] == color:\n                            input_grid[i][k + 1] = color\n                        else:\n                            break\n                    for k in range(i + 1, rows):\n                        if input_grid[k][j] == color:\n                            input_grid[k - 1][j] = color\n                        else:\n                            break\n                    for k in range(i - 1, -1, -1):\n                        if input_grid[k][j] == color:\n                            input_grid[k + 1][j] = color\n                        else:\n                            break\n                    input_grid[i][j] = black\n    return input_grid\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    In the input,