{"action": "edit", "code": "def _hole3(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds the first continuous row of input grid that has non-black point.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array of shape (n, m) representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A tuple of two integers representing the starting and ending indices of the first continuous row of input grid that has non-black point.\n    \"\"\"\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        if not np.all(input_grid[i] == black):\n            for j in range(i, input_grid.shape[0]):\n                if np.all(input_grid[j] == black):\n                    return (i, j - 1)\n            return (i, input_grid.shape[0] - 1)\n    return (0, 0)\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    In the input, you should see a n*n grid with multiple color pixels.\n    \"\"\"\n    ans_grid = modify_grid(input_grid)\n    ans_grid[:, 0] = 0\n    ans_grid[:, -1] = 0\n    return ans_grid\ndef modify_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Traverse all pixels, if a non-black pixel (x, y) is surrounded by black pixels, \n    then traverse all pixels in the row: if a pixel (x, k) with the same color and k != y.\n    Then if k>y, then paint (x, k-1) into this color,if k<y, paint (x,k+1). \n    Finally assign (x,y) to black. return the modified grid\n    \"\"\"\n    ans_grid = _hole3(input_grid)\n    ans_grid[:, 0] = 0\n    ans_grid[:, -1] = 0\n    return ans_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    In the input, you should see a n*n grid with multiple color pixels.\n    \"\"\"\n    ans_grid = `Traverse all pixels, if a non-black pixel (x, y) is surrounded by black pixels, then traverse all pixels in the row: if a pixel (x, k) with the same color and k != y.Then if k>y, then paint (x, k-1) into this color,if k<y, paint (x,k+1). Finally assign (x,y) to black. return the modified grid`(input_grid)\n    ans_grid[:, 0] = 0\n    ans_grid[:, -1] = 0    \n    return ans_grid\n    ", "gpt_code": "def _hole3(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds the first continuous row of input grid that has non-black point.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array of shape (n, m) representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A tuple of two integers representing the starting and ending indices of the first continuous row of input grid that has non-black point.\n    \"\"\"\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        if not np.all(input_grid[i] == black):\n            for j in range(i, input_grid.shape[0]):\n                if np.all(input_grid[j] == black):\n                    return (i, j - 1)\n            return (i, input_grid.shape[0] - 1)\n    return (0, 0)\ndef modify_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Traverse all pixels, if a non-black pixel (x, y) is surrounded by black pixels, \n    then traverse all pixels in the row: if a pixel (x, k) with the same color and k != y.\n    Then if k>y, then paint (x, k-1) into this color,if k<y, paint (x,k+1). \n    Finally assign (x,y) to black. return the modified grid\n    \"\"\"\n    ans_grid = _hole3(input_grid)\n    ans_grid[:, 0] = 0\n    ans_grid[:, -1] = 0\n    return ans_grid", "holes": {"modify_grid": "Traverse all pixels, if a non-black pixel (x, y) is surrounded by black pixels, then traverse all pixels in the row: if a pixel (x, k) with the same color and k != y.Then if k>y, then paint (x, k-1) into this color,if k<y, paint (x,k+1). Finally assign (x,y) to black. return the modified grid"}}
